    narr:narration """This hub gathers observations of the document's recurring [rule-of-three rhetoric](narr:StyleObs_rule_of_three) — triadic parallelism used for emphasis and memorability across a product pitch. The cleanest exemplars: the three product pillars [AI-Assisted Development / Executive Assistance / Content Generation](narr:StyleObs_RuleOfThree_UseCases), the [git-native triad](narr:Observation_GitNativeTriad) with parallel -able suffixes, and the [escalating-severity triad](narr:StyleObs_RuleOfThree) (supercharged → dumb → useless). The pattern also drives [audience lists](narr:StyleObs_4), [verb triads at the cursor](narr:StyleObs_10), and [parallel noun-phrase cadence](narr:StyleObs_cadence_1). Several observations note the device's purpose is scannable rhythm and a value prop deliverable in under thirty seconds. Note the mix of triad *types*: balanced/parallel (pillars, audiences), escalating (severity), and suffix-parallel (git). Not every instance is strictly three — and one child records a different compression pattern entirely.""" ;
